Putting it together, 242 = 2 × 11 × 11. So, 242 can be expressed as 2 × 11².

Since we have a perfect square (11²), that can be taken out of the square root. The formula for simplifying square roots is √(a² × b) = a√b. Applying that here, √(11² × 2) = 11√2.

Just to double-check, let's compute 11√2 numerically and see if squaring it gives us back 242.

First, calculate 11√2:

