Is this the simplest form? Let me see if 243 and 625 have any common factors.

243 is 3^5, and 625 is 5^4. Since 3 and 5 are prime numbers, they don't share any common factors besides 1. So, yes, 243/625 is already in its simplest form.

Therefore, the eighth term of the sequence is 243/625.

